%H A390535 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tetration">Tetration</a>.
%F A390535 For any given n > 1, let A013929(n) = p_1^q_1*p_2^q_2*...*p_k^q_k be the prime factorization of A013929(n), where p_1, p_2, ..., p_k are distinct primes. Then, a(n) <= p_1*p_2*...*p_k.
%e A390535 a(4) = 6 since the congruence speed of 6 does not converge to a fixed value in the radix-12 numeral system (it equals 0 at height 1, 3 at height 2, 23325 at height 3, and so forth).
